  "body": "## It would good to able to have a separated file structure in Truffle\r\n\r\nCurrently it's not possible to separate your code in Truffle in a meaningful way. I would like to be able to do like the below.\r\n\r\n```\r\n|____build\r\n|\r\n|____src\r\n| |\r\n| |____contracts\r\n| | |\r\n| | |\r\n| | |___media.sol\r\n| | |___rules.sol\r\n| | |___Migrations.sol\r\n| |\r\n| |\r\n| |____migrations\r\n|   |____1_initial_migration.js\r\n|   |____2_deploy_contracts.js \r\n| \r\n| \r\n|____test\r\n| |____media.js\r\n| |____rules.js\r\n| |____TestRules.sol\r\n|____truffle.js\r\n```\r\n\r\nAs the above structure shows, how you can separate the logic code which are the `contracts` and `migrations` files or any other business logic files say `api` in a separate folder in this case `src` for better modularity.\r\n\r\nCurrently Truffle does not allow this clear separation, but it would be good to able to do this, maybe it's already in the roadmap in that case I'd like to know.",
